          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "rohit jahagirdar"
          },
          "datePublished": "2021-03-24",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I will recommend MCPS school for the kids living around 5kms radius from this school.\nExtremely happy with the kind of syllabus pattern they have for kids.\nGood activities are conducted so the kids enjoy doing it and their level of interest is maintained.\nEach person working at school is caring and love the work they do. This includes teaching staff and non-teaching as well.\nSchool in turn advise parents not to push the child beyond the limit and let them learn at the speed kid likes. I have never seen like this.\nParents don't take second thought before taking addmission to this school.\nI wish All the Best for school.\nThank You Aalpaysh Sir and Rashmi Mam for setting up such a good school.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Mount Carmel Public School - Pimple Gurav"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Arvind Venkatachalam"
          },
          "datePublished": "2020-06-12",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Both my kids are studying in Mount Carmel Public School my kids experience with the school is Fantastic, The teachers are Professional, caring and well organized. The Principal Sir and Mam personally make sure they understand each and every kid in their school. The admissions process was outstanding, they really care and truly want the best for your child.\nEven during this covid situation the teachers and the Principal are not just waiting for things to happen, they had their teachers attend trainings to conduct online classes and they have started it.\nMakes me proud to be part of such a Institution who looks towards progression and teaches the same to their kids.\nI wish the school staff and the Principal's the best of my wishes.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
